Returns the difference of two doubles expressed in log space, that is, sumLogProb = log (e^a - e^b) = log e^a(1 - e^(b-a)) = a + log (1 - e^(b-a)) By exponentiating b-a, we obtain better numerical precision than we would if we calculated e^a or e^b directly.

sumLogProb(double, double) - 类 中的静态方法cc.mallet.util.Maths
Returns the sum of two doubles expressed in log space, that is, sumLogProb = log (e^a + e^b) = log e^a(1 + e^(b-a)) = a + log (1 + e^(b-a)) By exponentiating b-a, we obtain better numerical precision than we would if we calculated e^a or e^b directly.
